##Three-way sorter is a R Shiny gadget that allows users to upload a file containing items 
##to be sorted (each in a line). Then all items appear in the left box, and the users can
##select items and distribute them among three boxes, and then submit it by clicking "Click to sort"
##button to sort the items.  

Usage:
In bash,

R -e 'shiny::runApp("app.R")'

Then, copy the url to a browser, e.g., http://127.0.0.1:6864
